<br>
Shortblade + switftblade<br>
<br>
Reasoning:<br>
<br>
The swiftblade is in a different class than frosty or yak, and the shortblade yet again a jump up in quality. If for some reason you are able to acquire these now, you really should. To make an (admittedly lame) analogy, its like getting a mustang with turbo (proc) vs a porsche with a normally aspirated engine <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Also You are 54/55 so probably not tanking any raids yet.<br>
I'd say concentrate on dps now, and when you get to a point where you need to hold aggro consistently, then get some aggro weapons.<br>
Play a little sloppy with aggro. Make the rogues take a few hits between evades. Let the slowers tank for a round or two. They aren't going to die from it in any place where you are llikely to be MTing. Go for dps - kill faster - level faster.<br>
<br>
That being said, later, when you get to where aggro control really matters like fighting hard hitting PoP mobs or MTing raid mobs, then look into sacrificing (a lot) of dps for aggro procs - or perhaps by then a high-dps proc weapon will be available to you.<br>
<br>
Just my take on things<br>
<br>
Zacc-65-MM <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ghazad>GhazaD</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/11/03 1:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5434.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: If you could choose only 2.....</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the replys guys. I have been browsing this forum a lot lately and I am suddenly wondering if I should buy a Windblade instead of upgrading 1H.<br>
